FeedPackage.Description:
This nuget updates your AssemblyInfo.cs with data from git repository based on GitFlow model (http://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/), allowing you to create Semantic Versioning (http://semver.org/). It is basically a modification of GitVersion (https://github.com/ParticularLabs/GitVersion). Main differences are that using MSBuildCommunityTasks the AssemblyInfo.template.cs file is being changed with some variables being changed to proper version info, instead of creating completely new AssemblyInfo.cs.
Reasons are: * I don't like GitVersion full versioning (like 1.2.3+4.Branch.master.Sha.12345678901234567890), so I can use here my own versioning scheme (like 1.2.3+4.master.1234567) (without "branch", "sha" and with short SHA hash); * Automatically generated assemblies from GitVersion were not compatible with NETMF.
FeedPackage.Summary: This nuget updates your AssemblyInfo.cs with data from git repository based on GitFlow model with your own versioning schemas.
FeedPackage.Title: Ktos.Build.GitVersion

FeedPackage.Description:
This nuget updates your AssemblyInfo.cs with data from git repository based on GitFlow model (http://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/), allowing you to create Semantic Versioning (http://semver.org/). It is basically a modification of GitVersion (https://github.com/ParticularLabs/GitVersion). Main differences are that using MSBuildCommunityTasks the AssemblyInfo.template.cs file is being changed with some variables being changed to proper version info, instead of creating completely new AssemblyInfo.cs.
Reasons are: * I don't like GitVersion full versioning (like 1.2.3+4.Branch.master.Sha.12345678901234567890), so I can use here my own versioning scheme (like 1.2.3+4.master.1234567) (without "branch", "sha" and with short SHA hash); * Automatically generated assemblies from GitVersion were not compatible with NETMF.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: upgraded to newest GitVersion and MSBuildTasks
FeedPackage.Summary: This nuget updates your AssemblyInfo.cs with data from git repository based on GitFlow model with your own versioning schemas.
FeedPackage.Title: Ktos.Build.GitVersion

FeedPackage.Description: SoundFingerprinting is a C# framework that implements an efficient algorithm of audio identification. Designed for developers, enthusiasts, researchers in the fields of audio processing, data mining, digital signal processing.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Major changes in published modules. SoundFingerprinting project has been changed to represent a more granular approach on published modules (as well as project structures). Aside of mentioned structure major change, in terms of the functional improvements, additional query method is implemented to return time-sequence location from the discovered track. Its now possible to detect time location using QueryWithTimeSequenceInformation on both QueryService as well as QueryCommand objects. NAudio will no longer be published as a separate module, rather it will be the default audio service published with SoundFingerprinting libraries. Interfaces for query/fingerprint have changed as well, in order to not bother the user with too many query parameters passed during fingerprinting/querying. Previous interface definitions will no longer be supported.

FeedPackage.Description: The SoundTouch Library is originally written by Olli Parviainen in C++. Although a .NET wrapper library is available, this library aims to be a complete rewrite in C#.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: 1.9.2: * Improved SoundTouch::flush() function so that it returns precisely the desired amount of samples for exact output duration control * Redesigned quickseek algorithm for improved sound quality when using the quickseek mode. The new quickseek algorithm can find 99% as good results as the default full-scan mode, while the quickseek algorithm is remarkable less CPU intensive. * Added adaptive integer divider scaling for improved sound quality when using integer processing algorithm * Added support for parallel computation support via .NET 4.0 TPL for better performance in multicore systems. * Added support for multi-channel audio processing * Added support for cubic and shannon interpolation for rate and pitch shift effects besides the original linear interpolation, to reduce aliasing at high frequencies due to interpolation. Cubic interpolation is used as default for floating point processing, and linear interpolation for integer processing. * Fixed bug in anti-alias filtering that limited stop-band attenuation to -10 dB instead of <-50dB, and increased filter length from 32 to 64 taps to further reduce aliasing due to frequency folding. * Performance improvements in cross-correlation algorithm * Other bug and compatibility fixes
FeedPackage.Tags: SoundTouch sound stretch tempo pitch rate
FeedPackage.Title: SoundTouch.Net
